title: The Big Whifflesnooze
description: Cheer, distracted by other work, doesn't give her complete attention to a problem with the Whiffles. The mistake starts a chain of comical events that results in the Whiffles going into a one-hundred-year sleep that can only be rectified by an ancient chant.

title: Pato's Living Room
description: Pato's living room has a sofa, a table, a TV and a rug. Pato is settling down to watch television when his friends burst into his house. But Pato does not feel like having company, so he throws them out. In the end, he feels bad for leaving them out and asks them to come back in.

title: Colors
description: Pocoyo is building a tower of color blocks. Suddenly the red block speaks. The red block has a yellow friend, a blue friend and a green friend. Pocoyo looks for Pato so that he can see this, but when Pato arrives the "toridoris" have camouflaged themselves as tower blocks. Pocoyo is able to find them again with the help of the children, and looks for Pato once more.

title: Hiding
description: Bing is helping Flop in Padget's shop when he decides to hide from Flop! But what will happen when Bing hides in Padget's store room and gets locked in?

title: Clowning Around/Read All About It/Mom for a Day/Caillou Plays Baseball
description: Caillou visits Grandma who shows him a book about clowns she got from the library./Caillou and Mom go to the library for story time./Caillou helps Daddy look after Rosie./When Caillou notices that Dad and Grandpa are captivated by a baseball game on TV, he wants to get in on the excitement.

title: Pato Underwater
description: Pato packs his bag of toys and heads off to play with Octopus and Whale underwater. Unfortunately none of his toys work in the sea, and he doesn't like the food so he's all set to head back home. But then Whale shows Pato how fun things can be underwater once you get used to it. Pato has a wonderful time riding on Whale's back, bouncing on sea sponges and playing in a bubble. Finally Pocoyo and Elly arrive too and everyone has a splashy underwater party together.

title: Hide and Seek
description: Pocoyo wants to play hide and seek but he doesn't understand the rules of the game. His friends help him learn the game and Pocoyo is finally ready to go out and search for them. When Pocoyo finally finds them, they have prepared a surprise party that they can enjoy together.

title: Boot Castle/Avocado's Long Time Out/Tanks Giving
description: Findley discovers a boot that him and Lucas use as a castle./ When they hear Avocado has been put in her naughty crate, Lucas and Findley entertain her./ Lucas brings Dimples things from around the house so she doesn't feel left out.

title: Taz You Like It
description: Taz discovers pratfalls get him laughs and attention.

title: Pocoyolympics
description: Pocoyo, Elly and Pato stage their own version of the olympics - with a funny and very original variety of contests.

title: Who's Your Granny?
description: When Granny gets sick, Lola tries to take over her responsibilities.

title: Ice Lolly
description: It's hot today so Bing and Flop are having yummy delicious ice pops from Gilly. But what will happen to their ice pops when Bing and Flop are rescuing Froggy from the swimming pool in the garden?

title: The Staff of Wisdom
description: Mush-Mush is amazed by the way Mushpot uses his staff of wisdom and how awesome it makes him look. Mush-Mush wants to be as cool as Mushpot and asks him to lend him his staff of wisdom. But the staff comes with a lot of responsibilities.

title: Sandcastle
description: Bing and Flop are building sandcastles when Pando comes to help with Don the Dumpertruck! But what will happen when Pando realizes Don's starter key is being used as a decoration on Bing's sandcastle?

title: Findley's Bad Day
description: Findley is convinced House is out to get him.

title: Whale's Birthday
description: It's Whale's birthday. When all of Whale's presents get spoiled on the way to the party, Pocoyo, Elly and Pato are sad. But Whale is happy just to see them. Friends are what you need for a party!

title: The Dolly Vanishes
description: On an overnight train trip to visit Floyd at college, Lola's doll vanishes. Baby Bugs acts as a detective as he tries to solve the missing Edna mystery via a series of simple flashbacks, seen from each Baby Looney Tunes' point of view.

title: Thomas Blasts Off
description: It's rocket launch day and all the trains get to help deliver the big rocket parts, but when Thomas is assigned a tiny part, he puts it off to help the others with their more exciting parts, not realizing that his "small" task was just as important.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: A Sweet and Sour Day/Caillou's Puppet Show/Caillou's Collection
description: Caillou is helping Grandma water her flowers and fill the birdbath./Caillou and his friends Jason and Jeffrey make finger puppets at playschool and decide to put on a puppet show./In the park Caillou starts a new hobby - collecting rocks!

title: Spinning Webs
description: Lucas questions his spider-hood when he can't spin a web properly.

title: Christmas Far From Home
description: Yanko invites Pocoyo and friends to spend Christmas with him and they accept gladly. However, when they arrive they discover that it's not the ideal plan they had imagined. Everything is made of ice, they slip, it's very cold and the food is disappointing… things are a bit complicated, especially for Pato, who was expecting to spend Christmas next to a chimney with a hot chocolate. But they will soon learn that, in spite of slippery ice, frozen fish and falling into the cold Artic water, the truly important thing is to spend Christmas together.

title: Where I Live/A Good Friend/Just Like Me/Just In Time/Mr. Fixit
description: When an invitation for Clementine's party accidentally ends up at Sarah's, Caillou learns the differences between the addresses of the two homes./When Leo forgets his brand new toy dinosaur in the park, Daddy and Caillou go looking for it./When Clementine tells Caillou how much she likes her older brother, Billy, to teach her things, Caillou sets out to teach something to Rosie./When Caillou's dawdling causes he, Mom and Rosie to be late going to the park, they end up missing Leo./When the washing machine needs fixing, Caillou ends up helping Bob the repairman.

title: Jingly Shoes
description: Charlie really wants to try to walk and with the help of Bing's jingly shoes he takes his first steps! But what will happen when Coco suggests Charlie should keep them?

title: Pocoyo Dance
description: Pocoyo finds a radio. Pato does his funny, funky dance and Elly demonstrates her delicate ballet style. Pocoyo hears a tune he likes and finds his groove. Everyone can dance in their own special way!

title: Chalk Dinosaur
description: Bing wants to draw a big picture so Flop finds him some chalk to draw on the sidewalk outside their house. But what happens when a big rain cloud comes just as Bing's finished his chalk dinosaur?

title: Fly, Chase, Fly
description: Chep is disappointed Mush-Mush and Lilit are too busy leaf-gliding to play moss-ball with him, so he hangs out with a new weevil friend instead. But Chep's new friend must migrate with all the other weevils. Except he doesn't know how to fly! Chep must teach him to fly while overcoming his own secret fear of heights.

title: Traffic Jam
description: Pocoyo is pretending to be a traffic police officer. Aided by a traffic light and a whistle, he is trying to make his friends obey the signs and cross at the crosswalk. This is no easy task, however.

title: Caillou Goes Caroling/A Playschool Party/Caillou's Christmas Eve
description: Caillou goes out caroling for the very first time with Mommy, Daddy, Rosie, Grandpa and Grandma./It's a very special day at playschool as they celebrate the many ways of celebrating the holiday season./It's finally Christmas Eve and Caillou just can't wait for nighttime.

title: Shine, Lilit, Shine
description: The Beacon Mushroom that guides the Mushables back to Mushton in the dark has gone out. So Lilit lights up and stands in its place for the night and soon gets quite bored! Lilit's good deed has her regretting her gift she's basically just a lamp! But when her light goes out, Lilit instantly regrets regretting it: she wants her gift back!

title: Caillou's Song/Follow Me/Where's Caillou?
description: Caillou wants to learn to play a song on his little keyboard./Caillou tries to befriend his new classmate, Andy./Caillou wants someone to play with.

title: Not Yours
description: Bing's helping Flop pick up groceries in Padget's shop today. And while Flop is paying, Bing picks up a lolly and puts it in his pocket. But what happens when Flop explains to Bing that he has stolen the lolly?

title: Shadow of a Doubt
description: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is.

title: Bend it Like Petunia
description: The Baby Looney Tunes learn all about soccer from Floyd, who surprisingly is an enthused soccer expert. At first awkward, Baby Petunia works the hardest and displays the best sportsmanlike attitude, eventually becoming the very finest all-around soccer player of all the Baby Looney Tunes.

title: Farewell Friends
description: Pato is leaving: he's packed his bags, he's said goodbye to his room and all his things. He's had one last sniff of his favorite flowers and said goodbye to Caterpillar, Alien, Baby Bird and Sleepy Bird. And there's the plane he's leaving in…! One last chance to say good bye. Good bye Pato!!! Everyone is waving and saying goodbye. Pato gets in the plane. One last wave. It's so sad!!! The plane goes in a circle one super-quick time and then Pato's home again. Hooray. Time for a welcome home party - and for someone else to have a go!

title: Wonderful World
description: Nia shows Thomas and Diesel how much unique beauty exists in Sodor, which comes in handy when they need plants to beautify a Plaza in Vicarstown.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Waffle Cones for Whiffles
description: The Whiffles are too hot and tired to work because their daily treat, colorful ice in Waffles Cones delivered by the whimsical "Icelings," hasn't arrived - the Icelings have mysteriously disappeared. As the Care Bears search for them, Share volunteers to make the treats. It's much more than she can handle but she's determined to go-it-alone and not ask for help. Things get out of hand and Share ends up snared in Bluster's trap with the Icelings, who help her to realize that we get more done when we work together.

title: The Paint Problem
description: Thomas needs repainting and must be patient as he dries, even though he feels like he's missing out.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Wackily Ever After
description: Pocoyo and his friends are playing dressing up and the narrator decides to tell a story. The traditional fairy tale takes on a decidedly wacky hue as the characters all undercut the conventions with hilarious and surprising results.

title: The Yolk's on You
description: Daffy and Melissa team up to play jokes on the other babies.

title: Friends of the Forest
description: While they are enjoying the longest day of the summer, Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit realise that the forest is drying out. Worried, Mushpot explains to our friends that the Tree of Life, that regenerate the entire forest, is dying! There is only one Mushable who could help Mushpot to save the forest: Starmush. But the Mushelders haven't gotten along for years. Will they be able to put their differences aside in order to save the Tree of Life before it's too late?

title: Looks for Gilbert/Surprise Breakfast/Missing Sock/Goes to Work/Quarrel
description: Caillou is having a game of dinosaur hunter with Gilbert the cat./Caillou gets up early one morning./Caillou wants to wear his favorite socks, but one of them is missing./Caillou goes to work with Mom./Clementine comes over to play.

title: Card Bored Box
description: Faced with nothing to do, the babies use a cardboard box and their imaginations to make playtime fun.

title: Kite
description: Bing and Flop are in the park to fly Bing's Hoppity Voosh kite, and Bing is excited to fly it all by himself. Will Bing be able to?

title: Double Bubble
description: Pocoyo is enjoying blowing bubbles with his bubble maker. Elly wants to play too. They can't agree on who gets to play with it. Finally they realize that the best way to play is to share.

title: Who's on the Phone?
description: Pocoyo finds a phone. He has to work out what it's for, and who's on the other end of the line. It's Elly inviting everyone to a party!

title: Compost to Go
description: When Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit take their compost meals back to their home-tree to eat, they think they have made a great new discovery - compost to go! They set up a delivery service so everyone can eat at home too. It's so cool! Except Sushi-Mushi misses hosting everyone at the Food Snail, and everyone starts missing eating together.

title: Stuck in the Mud
description: When Fung and Miff spoil Mush-Mush's fun tunnel surprise he has been working on for ages, he wishes their day was ruined too. And then it is, because they are taken by Muddler! Now our Mushlers have to go on a rescue mission to save Fung and Miff.

title: Nobody's Perfect
description: When Cheer makes some simple mistakes, she begins to lose confidence in her piloting skills and herself. The self-doubt becomes so severe, she decides to step away from her role as pilot of the Cloudseeker. But the Team needs her, the Whiffles need her, and she must regain her self-confidence so they can stop Bluster's latest nefarious scheme.

title: The Garden
description: Pato is tending to his garden when Pocoyo arrives. Pocoyo wants to plant a flower so Pato lends him a gardening book so that he can follow the steps to make his plant grow. But Pocoyo doesn't pay attention to the book and, because of this, is only able to grow a ridiculous looking plant. Pato decides to help Pocoyo get his plant to grow and sprout flowers.

title: That's the Way the Windmill Blows!/Mecha Machine Makers!
description: The windmill isn't turning, which means Sunny Field Farm has no power. The windmill needs to turn again so Zee can launch his rocket!/Izzy and Timmy are making a bird caller for Grandma, but have trouble connecting pieces of their machine.

title: Show and Tell/Caillou the Magician/Caillou's Castle
description: Caillou has to decide on a nice surprise to bring to playschool for Show and Tell./Grandma shows Caillou a simple magic trick, which makes him decide to be a magician./Caillou wants to play castles and dragons, even though Gilbert isn't very keen on playing the dragon.

title: Crack In The Tank/Big Mouth/Art From The Heart
description: When Dimples and Weebiscuit's tank leaks, they are put into new homes. They learn to accept change so long as they are together./ Dimples is worried about a tank decoration of a shark in her new aquarium. Appearances can be deceptive./ Lucas turns teacher as he tries to teach Maizie how to paint. When she thinks she's no good, Lucas encourages her to find inspiration.

title: Caillou of the Antarctic/Deep Sea Caillou/Caillou in the Bayou
description: Caillou is playing with Jeffrey and Jason when he gets accidentally pushed down./There's a new girl named Lee Wun in playschool, but she's so shy she won't talk to anybody./The whole family is on the way to the beach but accidentally ends up on a trail through a swamp.

title: Voosh
description: Bing is vooshing with Hoppity around the garden, and Hoppity is vooshing higher and higher. But what happens when Hoppity vooshes so high that he disappears?

title: School Daze
description: The babies play pretend school in preparation for the real thing.

title: Cat
description: Bing loves playing with Arlo the cat, but what happens when Bing meets a new cat, who isn't so friendly?

title: Ghost Train
description: Percy has to deliver the mail on Halloween when everyone knows the legendary Ghost Train comes out! Thomas rolls along to help Percy face his fears, but when a "real" Ghost Train appears... things get almost spooky.
originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

title: Road Trip
description: On a mission to a remote area of the Silver Lining, Cheer questions the directions from Bedtime's maps. Everyone else backs Bedtime: he's never been wrong before! When the directions turn out to be wrong and lead them into danger, Cheer must trust her instincts to find a way out of the mess.

title: Where's Mars?/Emma's Extra Snacks/Lost and Found
description: Caillou and Daddy are finishing up a model of the solar system./Caillou is confused when Emma is allowed to have extra snacks./When things begin to go missing around the house Mommy blames Gilbert.

title: Too Hot to Handle
description: Findley can't resist some freshly baked cookies that are too hot to eat.

title: The Neat and the Sloppy
description: A study in contrasts enlivens this odd couple's antics. Baby Daffy is the compulsive mess maker, and Baby Sylvester is the cleanliness freak.

title: Lucas We Have a Problem/Egg-Scuse Me/Pokey Dokey
description: Lucas helps Bodhi fulfill her dream of touching a star./ Lucas finds an egg and decides to take care of it. But he learns that responsibility is hard./ When Avocado loses her beloved toy, Lucas and Findley are determined to cheer her up.
